<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>*shrugs*: My 2 cents on a good debate</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Gray Rage (DB)">Gray Rage (DB)</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:33 a.m. 25/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> *shrugs*: My 2 cents on a good debate<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1683" TARGET=_self>I do agree with you on that point...</A> (Holly Golightly (Petunia, Ogre Shaman))
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> I agree with you that the +/-4 lvl limit and the "loot only

<BR>&gt; 1 item" rules do take away from the roleplaying, there is
<BR>&gt; probably no "great" solution to stop rampant PKing.
<P>Open up the attacks for lower than 4...but with a HUGE exp and perhaps a faction cost. I personally think the 1 item loot is good and even that shoud be taken away if the Pkill was NOT done by the intended looter. 1 item and the current dough ont he body is just fine and it will keep the random pking down a bit making pking only a PLEASURE experience instead of a fiscal one.
<P>&gt; As long as there are groups like CC who only goal in-game is to
<BR>&gt; ruin the game for other people...well...rules like this will be
<BR>&gt; necessary.
<P>I dunno if they are ruining the game for others. I think they create an enemy situation that folks can llok forward to hunting and killing in retrobution. If you feel CC are jerkoffs and must pay for their crimes...then <a href="http://personal.lig.bellsouth.net/lig/g/r/grayrage/dbmain.htm">join DB</a> (or any of about 50 million other guilds who think they are terds---in game anyhow ;p) and get some PAYBACK. Yes...folks lose in battle....but if you are also in a group...expect to win sometimes too and if you are attacked you can call for aid on your guild hotline.
<P>&gt; I don't mind being killed to a PK who roleplays the murder (i.e.
<BR>&gt; you're people killed my parents blah blah blah), but mindless
<BR>&gt; PKing I don't like and it needs to be put in check.
<P>Disagree. I think the fun of Zek is looking over your shoulder. Monsters are fine and dandy but Players are the TRUE challenge. Now I DO think there should be factions so that you can count on at least your race not jumping you as that is silly and not in the spirit of the GAME.
<P>&gt; So whether these rules are not exactly consistent with
<BR>&gt; "real-life" roleplaying is besides the point. I can
<BR>&gt; live with them and can ignore their contradictory nature,
<BR>&gt; knowing that groups like CC are put in check.
<P>&gt; Holly.
<P>*shrugs* You are playing an evil character in on Zek, feel free to head our way for a visit.
<P>Graraige (Gray Rage)
<P>PS If you don't like my ideas, refer to DarkenBane's mascot below.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
